# SCPB Skill

A comprehensive skill for working with the SCP - Containment Breach (SCPCB) game source code.

## When to Use

Use this skill when:
- Working on SCPB source code (BlitzBasic/.bb files)
- Porting SCPB to WASM or other platforms
- Understanding game mechanics and SCP behaviors
- Modifying game systems (NPCs, maps, items, save/load)
- Debugging game issues
- Adding new SCP entities or features
- Working on the WASM port (scpcb.wat, scpcb.wasm)

## Project Overview

**SCP - Containment Breach** is a survival horror game based on the SCP Foundation fiction. Players escape a facility containing anomalous entities while managing:
- **Blink system**: Must periodically blink to avoid certain SCPs
- **Stamina**: Running depletes stamina
- **Inventory**: Items with drag-and-drop and combination system
- **Sanity/Injury**: Environmental effects on player
- **Multiple endings**: Based on choices and survival

### Project Facts

| Attribute | Value |
|-----------|-------|
| Language | BlitzBasic (Blitz3D v1.108) |
| Lines of Code | ~52,000 across 35 .bb files |
| Version | 1.3.11 |
| License | CC BY-SA 3.0 |
| Original Author | Joonas Rikkonen (Regalis) |

## Directory Structure

```
scpcb/
├── *.bb              # Main source files (35 files)
├── *.decls           # DLL interface declarations
├── GFX/              # Graphics assets
│   ├── map/          # Room meshes
│   ├── npcs/         # NPC models
│   ├── items/        # Item models
│   ├── menu/         # Menu assets
│   └── font/         # Fonts
├── SFX/              # Audio
│   ├── Music/        # Background music
│   └── Room/         # Ambient sounds
├── Data/             # Configuration
│   ├── rooms.ini     # Room definitions
│   ├── events.ini    # Event triggers
│   ├── NPCs.ini      # NPC spawn data
│   ├── SCP-294.ini   # Drink recipes
│   └── materials.ini # Material properties
└── Loadingscreens/   # Loading images
```

## File Hierarchy (by Complexity)

### Tier 1: Utilities (Easy)
- **Difficulty.bb** - Difficulty settings
- **KeyName.bb** - Key mapping constants
- **CPU_Details.bb** - CPU detection
- **FMod.bb** - Audio wrapper

### Tier 2: Low Complexity
- **Blitz_Basic_Bank.bb** - Memory bank helpers
- **Blitz_File_FileName.bb** - File utilities

### Tier 3: Medium Complexity
- **StrictLoads.bb** - Safe resource loading with error checking
- **AAText.bb** - Anti-aliased text rendering
- **Skybox.bb** - Sky rendering
- **DevilParticleSystem.bb** - Particle effects

### Tier 4: Graphics & Processing
- **LightMapPNG.bb** - PNG image processing
- **Particles.bb** - Particle effects
- **DrawPortals.bb** - Portal rendering

### Tier 5: Save/Load System
- **Save.bb** - Complex save/load serialization

### Tier 6: Audio & Video
- **MusicPlayer.bb** - Background music
- **LoadAllSounds.bb** - Sound loading

### Tier 7: UI & Menu
- **Menu.bb** - Main menu, settings, options
- **Achievements.bb** - Achievement system

### Tier 8: Game Mechanics
- **Items.bb** - Inventory and item system
- **Update.bb** - Network updates

### Tier 9: Level System
- **MapSystem.bb** - Procedural map generation

### Tier 10: AI System
- **NPCs.bb** - NPC AI with state machines

### Tier 11: Core Game Loop
- **Main.bb** - Entry point, initialization
- **UpdateEvents.bb** - Events, SCP behaviors

## SCP Entities

### SCP-173 - The Sculpture
```blitzbasic
; Moves only when not observed
; Can be frozen by eye contact
; Neck snapping attack
```
**Behavior:**
- Moves when player doesn't blink
- Speed increases over time
- Can be observed by other NPCs
- Teleports to random locations

### SCP-096 - The Shy Guy
```blitzbasic
; Killer when viewed
; Instant death if in view
;不可阻挡的追猎
```
**Behavior:**
- docile until viewed (screenshot, camera, or direct sight)
- Screams when disturbed
- Fast pursuit
- Can break through doors

### SCP-106 - The Old Man
```blitzbasic
; Corrosion attacks
; Can pull into dimension
; Slow but dangerous
```
**Behavior:**
- Emerges from walls/floors
- Causes corrosion damage
- Can drag player to pocket dimension
- Telegraphed attacks

### SCP-049 - The Plague Doctor
```blitzbasic
; Cures "pestilence"
; Lethal touch
; Revival mechanic
```
**Behavior:**
- Approaches player
- Demands to cure pestilence
- Touch kills player
- Can revive as SCP-049-2

### SCP-939 - With Many Voices
```blitzbasic
; Predators that mimic voices
; Pack behavior
; Multiple instances
```
**Behavior:**
- Mimics voices of other SCPs
- Pack coordination
- Cannot see (relies on sound)
- Fast and aggressive

## Game Systems

### Player Mechanics

```blitzbasic
; Core player variables (typically in Main.bb or globals)
Global PlayerRoom%
Global Collider%
Global Camera%

; Blink system
Global BlinkTimer#
Global BlinkEffect#

; Stamina
Global Stamina#
Const MAX_STAMINA = 100.0

; Health and status
Global Health#
Global Sanity#
Global Bleeding%

; Equipment
GlobalNVG%  ; Night vision goggles
Global GasMask%
Global Armor%
```

### Map System

```blitzbasic
; Zones
Const ZONE_LCZ% = 0  ; Light Containment Zone
Const ZONE_HCZ% = 1  ; Heavy Containment Zone
Const ZONE_EZ% = 2   ; Entrance Zone

; Room types
Const ROOM_COMMON% = 0
Const ROOM_SCP% = 1
Const ROOM_EXIT% = 2
```

### Inventory System

```blitzbasic
Type Items
    Field obj%
    Field ItemID%
    Field Name$
    Field Description$
    Field State%      ; 0=normal, 1=used, 2=combined
    Field State2%
End Type

; Drag and drop
; Item combination
; Keycards and access levels
```

## Type System Pattern

```blitzbasic
; Standard SCPCB Type definition
Type TEntityName
    Field obj%              ; 3D object handle
    Field obj2%             ; Secondary object
    Field Collider%         ; Collision entity
    Field ID%               ; Unique identifier
    Field Type%             ; Entity type
    Field State#            ; Primary state
    Field State2#           ; Secondary state
    Field State3#           ; Tertiary state
    Field Speed#            ; Movement speed
    Field CurrSpeed#        ; Current speed
    Field Path.WayPoints[20]  ; Pathfinding waypoints
    Field PathStatus%       ; Pathfinding state
    ; ... additional fields
End Type

; Access patterns
entity.TEntityName = New TEntityName
entity\obj = CreateMesh()
entity\Speed# = 5.0
entity\ID% = 123

For entity.TEntityName = Each TEntityName
    UpdateEntity(entity)
Next

Delete entity.TEntityName
```

